9. PAYMENT LIFECYCLE
==================================================
Implement a simple but realistic payment lifecycle.

APIs / operations:
A. Calculate pricing
POST /api/payments/calculate

Request:
- rentalId
- extraDiscountAmount optional
- discountReason optional
- penaltyAmount optional
- penaltyReason optional
- escrowDepositAmount
- currency optional

Response:
- rentalId
- numberOfDays
- dailyRate
- baseAmount
- discountAmount
- penaltyAmount
- finalAmount
- escrowDepositAmount
- totalAuthorizationAmount
- currency

B. Create payment
POST /api/payments

Behavior:
- fetch rental snapshot
- calculate pricing
- create Payment with status PENDING
- create EscrowAccount with status HOLD_REQUESTED
- create initial escrow ledger entry HOLD_CREATED
- return payment + escrow summary

C. Authorize payment
POST /api/payments/{paymentId}/authorize

Behavior:
- allowed only from PENDING
- move payment status to AUTHORIZED
- move escrow HOLD_REQUESTED to HELD
- add/keep hold reference
- record ledger if needed

D. Capture payment
POST /api/payments/{paymentId}/capture

Behavior:
- allowed only from AUTHORIZED
- move to CAPTURED

E. Fail payment
POST /api/payments/{paymentId}/fail

Behavior:
- allowed from PENDING or AUTHORIZED
- move to FAILED

F. Cancel payment
POST /api/payments/{paymentId}/cancel

Behavior:
- allowed from PENDING or AUTHORIZED
- move to CANCELLED
- if escrow was HELD, release it

G. Refund payment
POST /api/payments/{paymentId}/refund

Behavior:
- allowed only from CAPTURED
- move to REFUNDED

