10. ESCROW LIFECYCLE
==================================================
Implement clear escrow logic.

APIs / operations:
A. Release full escrow
POST /api/escrows/{rentalId}/release

Request:
{
  "reason": "Vehicle returned safely"
}

Behavior:
- allowed from HELD or PARTIALLY_RELEASED
- mark escrow as RELEASED
- set releasedAt
- create FULL_RELEASE ledger entry

B. Partial escrow deduction
POST /api/escrows/{rentalId}/deduct

Request:
{
  "amount": 500000,
  "entryType": "DAMAGE_DEDUCTION",
  "reason": "Scratch on front bumper"
}

Behavior:
- allowed from HELD or PARTIALLY_RELEASED
- amount must be positive and <= remaining deposit
- create deduction ledger entry
- if some balance remains, status = PARTIALLY_RELEASED
- if entire deposit is consumed, status = CONFISCATED

C. Open escrow dispute
POST /api/escrows/{rentalId}/dispute

Request:
{
  "reason": "Accident under investigation"
}

Behavior:
- allowed from HELD or PARTIALLY_RELEASED
- status = DISPUTED
- create DISPUTE_OPENED ledger entry

D. Get payment by rentalId
GET /api/payments/rental/{rentalId}

E. Get escrow by rentalId
GET /api/escrows/{rentalId}

